O-O-O Bd7 9. f4 h6 {Li Chao, one of the specialists of this opening chose this
move order in many of his games but I suggest playing without ...h6 because
h6-pawn prevents our bishop from developing to h6 in some variations.} 10. Bh4
b5 (10... Nxe4 $6 {This move lost its earlier popularity with the strenghtened
computers.} 11. Qe1 Nf6 12. Nf5 $1 $14) 11. Bxf6 gxf6 12. f5 {White aims to
