24. Be2 d4 25. Qe4 dxc3 26. bxc3 Qxc3 27. Qb7+ Qc7 28. Qxa6 Qc2+ 29. Ka1 Qc3+
30. Kb1 Qc2+ $11 {draw with perpetual check}) 20... a5 21. Rhf1 Rhf8 22. Rd3 {
[%cal Gd3c3,Gd3h3]} b4 23. Rh3 (23. Rg3 e5 24. Nf5+ Bxf5 25. Qxc5 Rxc5 26. Rxf5
h4 27. Rg6 Bg5 28. Rg7+ Rf7 29. Rg8 Rf8 30. Rg7+ Rf7 $11 {draw with move
repetition.}) 23... Bf4 $1 {[%cal Gf4e5] Black wants to put his bishop on e5.}
24. Qxf4 (24. Rxh5 $2 Be5 $17 {Black has a clear advantage.}) (24. Bxh5 $6 Be5
25. Nf3 Bb5 26. Qxc5 Rxc5 $15 {This endgame is slightly better for Black.})
24... e5 25. Qd2 Bxh3 26. Nb3 Qxc2+ 27. Qxc2 Rxc2 28. Kxc2 Bxg2 29. Rg1 Bxe4+
30. Kd1 (30. Bd3 Rc8+ 31. Kd2 Bxd3 32. Kxd3 a4 33. Nd2 d5 34. Rg7+ Ke6 35. Rb7
$8 e4+ 36. Kd4 Rc2 37. Rb6+ Kf7 38. Nf1 Rxb2 39. Kxd5 Rxa2 40. Rxb4 f5 41. Ke5
