-Vera Ruiz,H (2235) ICCF email 2015}) 14... Qxc6 $5 {[%cal Gd7e6] Black
captures with queen to ensure protection of e6-pawn with the d7-bishop.} 15.
Bd3 h5 {[%cal Gf8h6]} 16. Kb1 b4 (16... Bh6 $5 17. Qf2 Qc5 18. Qxf6 Qe5 19.
Qxe5 dxe5 $44 {Bishop pair and the counterplay on g-file gives Black a good
compensation for the pawn. Detailed information about this pawn structure can
