Qxc2+ 27. Qxc2 Rxc2 28. Kxc2 Bxg2 29. Rg1 Bxe4+ 30. Kd1 (30. Bd3 Rc8+ 31. Kd2
Bxd3 32. Kxd3 a4 33. Nd2 d5 34. Rg7+ Ke6 35. Rb7 $8 e4+ 36. Kd4 Rc2 37. Rb6+
Kf7 38. Nf1 Rxb2 39. Kxd5 Rxa2 40. Rxb4 f5 41. Ke5 f4 42. Rxe4 Rf2 43. Rxf4+
Rxf4 44. Kxf4 a3 45. Nd2 a2 46. Nb3 h4 47. Kg4 Kg6 48. Kxh4 Kh6 $11) 30... f5
$13 {This complicated endgame is probably a draw with accurate play as the
corrospondence game shows.} 31. Nd2 Bd5 32. Rg7+ Rf7 33. Rg6 Be6 34. Nc4 Rh7
35. Nxa5 Kf7 36. Rg5 h4 37. Bh5+ Kf6 38. Rg6+ Ke7 39. Be2 Kf7 40. Rg2 h3 41.
Rg5 f4 42. Bd3 Rh8 43. Rg6 d5 44. Nc6 e4 45. Ne5+ Ke7 46. Bf1 d4 47. Nc6+ Kf7
48. Ne5+ Ke7 49. Nc6+ {1/2 (49) Martin Vazquez,J (2351)-Vera Ruiz,H (2235)
ICCF email 2015} *

