{When this structure appears on the board, the queens are already exchanged.
This position on the diagram arises out of structure 4 when Black allows the
move Qxf6 in order to answer it with ...Qe5. In this way, he manages to
exchange the queens. Practice has shown that Black has enough compensation for
the pawn. The doubled pawns on the e-file are not a weakness at all. They
control a number of important squares in the center. Additionally, Black has a
pair of bishops and active play on the g-file.}  *

