typical pawn sacrifice gives Black good compensation.} (11... gxf6 $6 12. Nxc6
Bxc6 13. Bd3 $14 {[%csl Re7] This position is slightly better for White
because our bishop on e7 is not on its ideal location. As we have seen man
times, it is not good in this pawn structure to develop this bishop from e7
very early. After White employs his main idea f5, the h6-c1 diagonal is opened
for this bishop and Black wants to be able to play ...Bh6. Therefore, leaving
the bishop on f8 rather than developing it to e7 is better. Instead Black can
play moves like ...Qb7-Qc5, ...b4 and ...a5.}) 12. Nxc6 Bxc6 13. Qxd6 Qxd6 14.
