preparations with this natural move before pushing f5.} (14. Rhe1 h5 15. Bc4 $5
{[%cal Gd2d3,Ge2d4,Gf4f5] White has no alternative plan other than this move.
White brings the bishop to the ideal square on c4 and threatens to play Qd3,
Nd4 and f5. But White can realize this move by losing a pawn which is not a
problem for Black.} Bxe4 $1 {We have to accept the pawn sacrifice or otherwise
White will reach its aim.} (15... Qc5 $2 16. Qd3 a5 17. Nd4 Bd7 18. f5 $16 {
The dream position for White. All the pieces are ideally located and are
