1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 Nc6 6. Bg5 e6 7. Qd2 a6 8.
O-O-O Bd7 9. f4 b5 10. Bxf6 gxf6 11. Nxc6 Bxc6 12. Qe3 {This move has various
purposes. The most important is to prevent the black queen from reaching b6.
Furthermore, as in the 12.Qe1, this move prepares Nd5. Apart from these ideas,
after White's main idea f5, White may play Qh3 to attack e6-pawn.} Qe7 $1 {
[%cal Ge7a7,Ga7c5] This is the best reaction for Black. With this move, Black
prevents the Nd5 idea and tries to bring the queen to its ideal square by
means of ... Qa7-Qc5.} 13. Bd3 {This is by far the most popular and most
logical developing move.} (13. a3 {White would like to prevent ...b4 before
completing the development but this variation does not cause any danger for
Black.} Rb8 14. Bd3 Bg7 15. Qg3 O-O $1 16. Qh4 b4 17. axb4 Rxb4 18. Rhf1 {
