{[#] In this position White is threatening to play g4-g5. What is the best way
for Black to prevent it?} 16... g5 $3 {An incredible idea! Black is not afraid
of weakening his king's position. With this move, Black has prevented the
g5-threat and can try to dominate the dark squares.} 17. e5 $6 {This dubious
pawn sacrifice does not give White enough compensation.} (17. fxg5 Qxg5 $15 {
Black has a slightly better position.}) (17. f5 Qe5 $15 {[%cal Ge7f6] Black is
ready to play ...Bf6.}) (17. h4 gxf4 18. g5 Qe5 19. Rxf4 Rab8 $15 {[%cal Ga5a4]
Black wants to play ...a4 with a better position.}) 17... dxe5 18. f5 {1/2 (23)
Moldovan,D (2400)-Nevednichy,V (2525) Herculane 1996} Rfd8 $1 $146 {[%cal
Ge5e4] Black is threatening to play ...e4.} 19. fxe6 Qxe6 20. Ng3 e4 21. Rfe1
Bd5 22. Nxe4 Bxa2+ 23. Ka1 Bc4 $19 {Black has a winning advantage.} *

