{[#] Black's knight on h5 is under attack and it is not so easy to find a good
way to protect it. So how should Black continue here?} 18... Nf6 $3 {Thanks to
this unexpected and marvelous idea Black gets a very good game.} 19. Bh3 (19.
gxf6 $2 {It is a big mistake to accept the piece sacrifice.} Bxf6 20. Qd2 (20.
Qxd6 Bxc3 21. bxc3 (21. Qxc7 Bxb2+ 22. Kd2 Rxc7 $19 {White's king is very bad.
Black has a winning position.}) 21... Qxc3 22. Qd3 Qa5 $19 {[%cal Ga5a2] White
has no defence.} 23. Qxd7 Qa3+ 24. Kd2 Rxc2+ $1 25. Kxc2 Rb2+ 26. Kc1 Qc3#)
20... Rxb2 $1 {After this move we enter a forced sequence resulting in an
endgame with a big edge for Black.} 21. Bd4 Bxd4 22. Qxd4 Rxa2 23. Rh2 Qxc3 24.
Qxc3 Rxc3 25. Rxd6 Rc7 26. Rhd2 Rb7 {[%cal Ga2a1]} 27. R2d3 Be8 $17 {[%cal
Gg8f8,Gf8e7,Gb7c7] Black is planning to play ...Kf8-e7, ...Rc7. Black has a
clear advantage.}) 19... d5 $5 {Black can continue to play on instead of
making a draw.} ({If Black wants he can make a draw with} 19... Nh5 $11) 20.
Qd3 (20. gxf6 $2 Bxf6 21. Qc5 Qb7 22. Qa3 Be7 23. Qb3 Qc7 $17 {[%csl Rb3]
White's queen is trapped.}) 20... Nh5 21. exd5 Nf4 22. Bxf4 Qxf4+ 23. Rd2 Bb4
24. dxe6 Bxe6 25. Bxe6 fxe6 ({Again, if Black wants he can make a draw with} 
25... Rxc3 26. bxc3 Ba3+ 27. Kd1 Rb1+ 28. Ke2 Rxh1 29. Qf5 Rh2+ 30. Kf1 Rh1+
31. Ke2 Rh2+ $11 {Draw by perpetual check.}) 26. Qe4 Qxe4 27. Nxe4 (27. fxe4 $4
{is a blunder and Black wins after:} Rxc3 28. bxc3 Ba3+ 29. Kd1 Rb1+ 30. Ke2
Rxh1 $19) 27... Bxd2+ 28. Nxd2 Rf8 $13 {[%cal Gf8f4] The position is far from
clear, but Black will play ...Rf4 with good prospects.} *

